\v 9 By reason of the multitude of oppressions they make \add the oppressed\add* to cry: they cry out by reason of the arm of the mighty. 
\v 10 But none saith, Where \add is\add* God my maker, who giveth songs in the night; 
\v 11 Who teacheth us more than the beasts of the earth, and maketh us wiser than the fowls of heaven? 
\v 12 There they cry, but none giveth answer, because of the pride of evil men. 
